Oh, please! I'm going to be sick!

01:19:44.095 --> 01:19:46.063
You shouldn't have done that.

01:19:46.598 --> 01:19:48.896
- I hate hypocrisy.
- That was cruel and vicious.

01:19:49.100 --> 01:19:51.034
She'll get over it. She'll recover.

01:19:51.236 --> 01:19:52.794
- And damaging to me.
- To you!

01:19:53.004 --> 01:19:53.800
To me!

01:19:56.775 --> 01:20:01.269
Beautiful. You got to have a swine
to show you where the truffles are.

01:20:01.980 --> 01:20:05.108
Rearrange your alliances.
Make the best of things.

01:20:05.450 --> 01:20:06.883
Put your wife in the car.

01:20:07.219 --> 01:20:09.619
I've had enough rides tonight.
We'll walk.

01:20:09.955 --> 01:20:11.946
Right, you go plan some new strategy.

01:20:14.059 --> 01:20:15.185
You'll regret this.

01:20:15.393 --> 01:20:16.985
No doubt. I regret everything.

01:20:17.462 --> 01:20:19.430
No, I mean I'll make you regret this.

01:20:19.631 --> 01:20:20.461
Clean up the mess.

01:20:20.966 --> 01:20:21.955
You just wait.

01:20:23.635 --> 01:20:25.398
- Very good, George.
- Thank you.

01:20:25.637 --> 01:20:27.935
- Really good!
- I'm glad you enjoyed it.

01:20:28.139 --> 01:20:32.667
I mean, you did a good job.
You really fixed it.

01:20:34.312 --> 01:20:36.803
That's the most life you've shown
in a long time.

01:20:37.148 --> 01:20:38.479
You bring out the best in me.

01:20:42.487 --> 01:20:44.318
You really are a bastard!

01:20:44.656 --> 01:20:47.147
You can go around like
a hopped-up Arab...

01:20:47.993 --> 01:20:51.156
...slashing at everything,
scarring up half the world...

01:20:51.463 --> 01:20:54.057
...but let somebody else try it?
Oh no!

01:20:54.332 --> 01:20:58.496
Why, baby, I did it all for you!
I thought you'd like it, sweetheart.

01:20:59.337 --> 01:21:01.828
It's to your taste,
blood, carnage and all.

01:21:02.407 --> 01:21:04.500
I thought you'd sort of get excited.

01:21:04.843 --> 01:21:08.176
Heave and pant and come running at me,
your melons bobbling...

01:21:08.513 --> 01:21:10.845
You have really screwed up, George.

01:21:11.516 --> 01:21:13.177
I mean it! You really have!

01:21:14.452 --> 01:21:16.181
You can sit,
gin running from your mouth...

01:21:16.521 --> 01:21:20.514
...you can humiliate me, tear me to
pieces all night, it's perfectly okay.

01:21:20.859 --> 01:21:22.019
You can stand it!

01:21:22.360 --> 01:21:23.349
I cannot stand it!

01:21:23.695 --> 01:21:26.528
You can stand it!
You married me for it!

01:21:29.534 --> 01:21:31.365
That's a desperately sick lie.

01:21:31.703 --> 01:21:33.694
Don't you know it even yet?

01:21:37.042 --> 01:21:39.374
My arm's gotten tired whipping you.

01:21:40.378 --> 01:21:42.869
- Year after year!
- Deluded, Martha.

01:21:43.214 --> 01:21:44.203
It's not what I wanted.

01:21:44.549 --> 01:21:47.211
I thought at least you were onto
yourself. I didn't know.

01:21:47.886 --> 01:21:49.217
No. You're sick!

01:21:51.056 --> 01:21:53.684
I'll show you who's sick!

01:22:08.907 --> 01:22:12.240
You really are having
a field day, aren't you?

01:22:13.912 --> 01:22:17.245
Well, I'm gonna finish you
before I'm through with you.

01:22:17.749 --> 01:22:20.741
You and that quarterback?
You both going to finish me?

01:22:20.952 --> 01:22:25.252
Before I'm through with you you'll
wish you'd died in that automobile!

01:22:25.590 --> 01:22:27.922
You'll wish you'd never mentioned
our son.

01:22:28.226 --> 01:22:28.954
I warned you.

01:22:29.194 --> 01:22:31.594
- I'm impressed!
- I warned you not to go too far!

01:22:31.796 --> 01:22:34.026
I'm just beginning!

01:22:34.599 --> 01:22:37.762
I'm numbed so I can take you
when we're alone. I don't listen.

01:22:38.436 --> 01:22:42.930
And if I do listen I sift it so I don't
really hear, which is the only way.

01:22:44.275 --> 01:22:46.766
But you've taken a new tack
in the last century...

01:22:47.112 --> 01:22:50.445
...which is just too much. Too much!

01:22:52.283 --> 01:22:56.447
I don't mind your dirty underthings in
public. I do, but I'm reconciled to it.

01:22:56.955 --> 01:23:00.118
You've moved into your own
fantasy world! You don't know...

01:23:00.959 --> 01:23:02.290
- You have!
- Nuts!

01:23:02.627 --> 01:23:03.787
You can go on...

01:23:04.129 --> 01:23:08.463
Have you ever listened to your
sentences? You're so convoluted.

01:23:09.134 --> 01:23:11.466
You talk like one of your stupid papers.

01:23:11.803 --> 01:23:14.966
Actually, I'm rather worried about you.
About your mind.

01:23:15.306 --> 01:23:17.797
Don't you worry
about my mind, sweetheart!

01:23:18.143 --> 01:23:19.132
I'll commit you.

01:23:19.644 --> 01:23:20.576
You what?

01:23:20.979 --> 01:23:22.970
I think I'll have you committed.

01:23:26.818 --> 01:23:28.979
Baby, aren't you something?

01:23:29.654 --> 01:23:31.485
I've got to find a way to get at you.

01:23:31.823 --> 01:23:35.315
You've got at me, you don't have to
do anything, George.

01:23:35.994 --> 01:23:38.326
A thousand years of you
has been enough!

01:23:38.663 --> 01:23:39.652
You'll go quietly then?

01:23:41.166 --> 01:23:44.658
Do you want to know what's
really happened?

01:23:45.503 --> 01:23:49.496
It snapped! Finally. Not me, it!
The whole arrangement.

01:23:50.175 --> 01:23:53.338
You can go on forever and ever,
everything is manageable.

01:23:53.678 --> 01:23:57.512
You make all sorts of excuses:
“To hell with it, this is life.”

01:23:57.749 --> 01:24:00.013
“Maybe tomorrow he'll be dead.
Maybe tomorrow you'll be dead.”

01:24:00.552 --> 01:24:02.019
All sorts of excuses.

01:24:02.887 --> 01:24:04.582
Then one day...

01:24:04.789 --> 01:24:07.417
...one night, something happens...

01:24:08.126 --> 01:24:09.150
...and snap!

01:24:09.360 --> 01:24:12.693
It breaks and you just don't
give a damn anymore!

01:24:14.699 --> 01:24:17.691
I tried with you, baby. I really tried.

01:24:18.536 --> 01:24:19.696
Come off it.

01:24:23.541 --> 01:24:25.372
You're a monster. You are.

01:24:26.745 --> 01:24:28.542
I'm loud, and I'm vulgar...

01:24:28.880 --> 01:24:32.043
...and I wear the pants in the house
because somebody's got to!

01:24:33.151 --> 01:24:35.051
But I am not a monster!

01:24:36.054 --> 01:24:37.043
I'm not!

01:24:37.388 --> 01:24:41.290
You're a spoiled, self-indulgent,
dirty-minded, liquor-riddled...

01:24:41.593 --> 01:24:43.720
Snap! It went snap.

01:24:44.395 --> 01:24:46.886
I won't try to get through
to you any more.

01:24:48.066 --> 01:24:51.001
There was a second back there,
when I could've...

01:24:51.236 --> 01:24:52.726
...gotten through to you.

01:24:53.371 --> 01:24:56.738
When maybe we could've out
through all this crap!

01:24:57.909 --> 01:25:01.572
But it's past.
And I'm not going to try.

01:25:01.913 --> 01:25:04.746
Once a month, Martha.
I've gotten used to it.

01:25:05.316 --> 01:25:10.049
We get Misunderstood Martha, the
good-hearted girl beneath the barnacles.

01:25:10.255 --> 01:25:13.588
The little miss that a touch of kindness
will bring to bloom again.

01:25:14.759 --> 01:25:18.422
I believed it more times than I'd admit.
I'm that much of a sucker.

01:25:19.097 --> 01:25:21.759
But I don't believe you,
I just don't believe you!

01:25:22.100 --> 01:25:25.934
There is no moment any more
when we could come together.

01:25:26.271 --> 01:25:29.934
You can't come together with nothing.
And you're nothing!

01:25:30.441 --> 01:25:31.430
Snap!

01:25:33.111 --> 01:25:35.773
I looked at you tonight
and you weren't there!

01:25:37.282 --> 01:25:41.616
It finally snapped.
And I'm gonna howl it out!

01:25:42.120 --> 01:25:43.610
I won't give a damn what I do.

01:25:43.955 --> 01:25:47.447
And I'll make the biggest goddamn
explosion you've ever heard!

01:25:48.126 --> 01:25:49.923
And I'll beat you at your own game.

01:25:50.295 --> 01:25:53.093
- Is that a threat, George?
- That's a threat, Martha.

01:25:53.298 --> 01:25:54.663
You're going to get it, baby!

01:25:54.866 --> 01:25:57.130
Be careful, I'll rip you to pieces.

01:25:57.502 --> 01:26:00.630
You are not man enough.
You haven't the guts!

01:26:02.140 --> 01:26:03.129
Total war?

01:26:03.942 --> 01:26:05.239
Total!

01:30:16.127 --> 01:30:16.957
Bells.

01:30:21.466 --> 01:30:23.957
I've been hearing bells!

01:30:25.470 --> 01:30:26.801
Bells ringing.

01:30:37.648 --> 01:30:39.809
And I couldn't sleep for the bells.

01:30:43.754 --> 01:30:45.381
That woke me up.

01:30:45.823 --> 01:30:47.017
What time is it?

01:30:47.758 --> 01:30:49.191
Don't bother me.

01:30:52.997 --> 01:30:54.328
I was asleep.

01:30:55.500 --> 01:30:58.162
And I was dreaming of something...

01:30:58.836 --> 01:30:59.996
...and I heard the sounds coming...

01:31:00.271 --> 01:31:02.637
...and I didn't know what it was...

01:31:04.041 --> 01:31:05.474
...and it frightened me.

01:31:06.177 --> 01:31:08.008
I'm going to get you, Martha.

01:31:10.014 --> 01:31:11.504
Somehow, Martha.

01:31:12.683 --> 01:31:16.847
And there was someone there and...
I didn't want someone there.

01:31:17.355 --> 01:31:19.016
I was naked.

01:31:19.357 --> 01:31:21.188
You don't know what's going on, do you?

01:31:22.226 --> 01:31:23.921
I don't want to know.

01:31:25.029 --> 01:31:26.360
Listen to them!

01:31:26.931 --> 01:31:28.694
- I don't want to!
- Look at them!

01:31:33.371 --> 01:31:35.032
I don't want any children.

01:31:36.040 --> 01:31:38.235
I don't want any children, please!

01:31:39.210 --> 01:31:42.702
I'm afraid. I don't want to be hurt.

01:31:45.216 --> 01:31:46.877
I should have known.

01:31:48.052 --> 01:31:50.543
Does that stud you married
know about that?

01:31:51.556 --> 01:31:54.719
How do you make your
secret little murders? Pills?

01:31:55.059 --> 01:31:58.051
You got a secret supply of pills?
Apple jelly? Willpower?

01:31:58.396 --> 01:31:59.294
Going to throw up?

01:31:59.497 --> 01:32:01.658
Where is he? I want my husband!
I want a drink!

01:32:01.866 --> 01:32:03.891
That's right, go at it!

01:32:04.735 --> 01:32:06.896
You know what's going on there?

01:32:08.906 --> 01:32:12.899
I don't want to know anything.
You leave me alone.

01:32:14.912 --> 01:32:15.810
Who rang?

01:32:16.747 --> 01:32:18.237
What were the bells? Who rang?

01:32:18.583 --> 01:32:20.380
He's up there and you ask who rang?

01:32:20.585 --> 01:32:22.018
Someone rang!

01:32:26.357 --> 01:32:27.722
Someone rang.

01:32:30.761 --> 01:32:32.786
The bells rang and it was someone...

01:32:32.997 --> 01:32:34.157
Somebody.

01:32:35.600 --> 01:32:38.433
Somebody rang.
The bells rang and it was somebody...

01:32:43.608 --> 01:32:44.632
I've got it!

01:32:45.710 --> 01:32:47.337
I've got it, Martha!

01:32:47.945 --> 01:32:50.379
It was a message. The message was...

01:32:50.615 --> 01:32:53.948
...our son... it was a message...
The bells rang...

01:32:54.151 --> 01:32:56.312
...and it was a message.
And it was about...

01:32:56.954 --> 01:32:58.387
...our son...

01:32:58.623 --> 01:33:00.352
And the message was...

01:33:02.960 --> 01:33:04.587
...our son...

01:33:04.929 --> 01:33:07.124
...is dead!

01:33:07.331 --> 01:33:10.164
Our son is dead
and I haven't told Martha!

01:33:10.468 --> 01:33:13.631
Our son is dead, Martha doesn't know,
and you won't tell her!

01:33:16.474 --> 01:33:19.807
I'll tell her myself.
In good time I'll tell her myself.

01:33:20.144 --> 01:33:21.475
I'm going to be sick.

01:33:22.146 --> 01:33:23.443
Are you? That's nice.

01:33:23.648 --> 01:33:26.981
- I'm going to die.
- Good, go right ahead.

01:33:35.993 --> 01:33:37.517
Martha, I have some...

01:33:38.195 --> 01:33:39.662
...terrible news.

01:33:41.832 --> 01:33:43.424
It's about our son.

01:33:45.436 --> 01:33:46.494
He's dead.

01:33:49.173 --> 01:33:50.697
Do you hear me, Martha?

01:33:52.843 --> 01:33:54.538
Our boy is dead.

01:34:46.897 --> 01:34:49.388
Where the hell is everybody?

01:35:46.290 --> 01:35:50.624
I'll give you bastards five to come from
wherever you're hiding!

01:37:06.370 --> 01:37:08.702
By God, you've gone crazy too.

01:37:11.041 --> 01:37:13.532
I said you've gone crazy too.

01:37:17.214 --> 01:37:18.545
Probably.

01:37:21.285 --> 01:37:22.650
You've all gone crazy.

01:37:24.255 --> 01:37:26.246
I come downstairs and what happens?

01:37:34.798 --> 01:37:36.265
What happens?

01:37:40.738 --> 01:37:44.538
My wife's in the can with
a liquor bottle and she winks at me.

01:37:45.743 --> 01:37:47.074
Winks at me!

01:37:48.245 --> 01:37:50.076
She's never winked at you?

01:37:51.081 --> 01:37:52.912
What a shame!

01:37:53.918 --> 01:37:57.410
She's lying down on the floor,
on the tiles, all curled-up...

01:37:59.089 --> 01:38:02.525
...and she starts peeling
the label on the brandy bottle.

01:38:02.726 --> 01:38:05.593
Maybe she'd be
more comfortable in the tub.

01:38:08.599 --> 01:38:11.261
And I asked her what she's doing
and she goes...

01:38:11.602 --> 01:38:14.093
...”Sshh, nobody knows I'm here.”

01:38:16.774 --> 01:38:18.765
And I come down here...

01:38:19.109 --> 01:38:23.603
...and you're stumbling around going
“clink”, for God's sake, “clink”.

01:38:26.951 --> 01:38:28.782
You've all gone crazy.

01:38:30.821 --> 01:38:32.288
Sad but true.

01:38:33.791 --> 01:38:35.622
Where is your husband?

01:38:35.960 --> 01:38:38.793
He is vanished.

01:38:44.802 --> 01:38:46.565
You're all crazy.

01:38:47.338 --> 01:38:48.396
Nuts!

01:38:49.139 --> 01:38:52.973
'Tis the refuge we take
when the unreality of the world...

01:38:53.310 --> 01:38:55.642
...sits too heavy on our tiny heads.

01:38:57.815 --> 01:39:01.808
Relax! Sink into it. You're no better
than anybody else.

01:39:03.487 --> 01:39:04.818
I think I am.

01:39:10.628 --> 01:39:14.155
You're certainly a flop
in some departments.

01:39:23.507 --> 01:39:24.667
What'd you say?

01:39:26.677 --> 01:39:29.168
I said you're a flop
in some departments.

01:39:29.513 --> 01:39:31.174
I'm sorry you're disappointed.

01:39:31.849 --> 01:39:34.340
Maybe some time
when I didn't drink for ten hours.

01:39:35.519 --> 01:39:38.181
Baby, you sure are a flop!

01:39:39.356 --> 01:39:42.348
You're something. You know that?
You're really something!

01:39:45.129 --> 01:39:47.029
To you, everybody's a flop!

01:39:47.364 --> 01:39:48.854
Your husband's a flop, I'm a flop.

01:39:49.199 --> 01:39:50.188
You're all flops.

01:39:50.534 --> 01:39:54.368
I am the Earth Mother
and you are all flops.

01:39:59.543 --> 01:40:01.534
I disgust me.

01:40:09.053 --> 01:40:12.545
There's only been one man in my life
who's ever made me happy.

01:40:14.725 --> 01:40:16.556
You know that? One.

01:40:17.227 --> 01:40:19.058
The gym instructor or something?

01:40:22.399 --> 01:40:23.331
George.

01:40:26.403 --> 01:40:27.734
My husband.

01:40:28.238 --> 01:40:29.398
You're kidding?

01:40:30.574 --> 01:40:32.405
You must be. Him?

01:40:35.913 --> 01:40:37.244
You don't believe it.

01:40:37.581 --> 01:40:38.912
Why, of course I do.

01:40:39.450 --> 01:40:41.247
You always deal on appearances?

01:40:41.518 --> 01:40:42.746
For God's sake!

01:40:44.254 --> 01:40:47.917
George who is out
somewhere there in the dark.

01:40:49.259 --> 01:40:52.092
Who is good to me. Whom I revile.

01:40:53.597 --> 01:40:58.261
Who can keep learning the games we play
as quickly as I can change them.

01:40:58.936 --> 01:41:02.099
Who can make me happy
and I do not wish to be happy.

01:41:02.439 --> 01:41:05.101
Yes, I do wish to be happy.

01:41:07.377 --> 01:41:09.368
George and Martha.

01:41:10.447 --> 01:41:12.608
Sad, sad, sad.

01:41:15.119 --> 01:41:17.952
Whom I will not forgive
for having come to rest.

01:41:18.622 --> 01:41:20.954
For having seen me and having said...

01:41:21.959 --> 01:41:24.450
...”Yes, this will do.”

01:41:25.629 --> 01:41:29.121
Who has made the hideous, the hurting...

01:41:29.466 --> 01:41:33.960
...the insulting mistake of loving me.

01:41:34.805 --> 01:41:36.636
And must be punished for it.

01:41:42.479 --> 01:41:45.312
Sad, sad, sad.

01:41:49.153 --> 01:41:50.142
Some day...

01:41:52.322 --> 01:41:53.482
...some night...

01:41:53.824 --> 01:41:58.158
...some stupid liquor-ridden night
I will go too far.

01:41:59.496 --> 01:42:03.489
I'll either break his back or I'll
push him off for good, which I deserve.

01:42:04.835 --> 01:42:06.826
I don't think he's got
a vertebrae intact.

01:42:08.338 --> 01:42:11.034
Oh, you don't?

01:42:11.241 --> 01:42:12.936
You don't think so?

01:42:13.844 --> 01:42:15.334
Oh, little boy!

01:42:16.180 --> 01:42:19.672
You've got yourself so hunched over
your microphone...

01:42:20.017 --> 01:42:21.348
Microscope!

01:42:21.685 --> 01:42:24.017
Yes. And you don't
see anything, do you?

01:42:24.354 --> 01:42:27.016
You see everything
but the goddamn mind.

01:42:27.357 --> 01:42:31.691
You see all the specks and the crap,
but you don't see what goes on, do you?

01:42:33.030 --> 01:42:37.023
You know so little. And you're going
to take over the world, huh?

01:42:37.534 --> 01:42:39.024
I said, all right!

01:42:41.038 --> 01:42:43.029
The stallion's mad, huh?

01:42:43.373 --> 01:42:46.706
The gelding's getting all upset, huh?

01:42:47.044 --> 01:42:49.035
You swing wild, don't you?

01:42:49.379 --> 01:42:51.040
You poor little bastard!

01:42:51.381 --> 01:42:52.712
Hit out at everything!

01:42:53.383 --> 01:42:54.714
Go answer the door.

01:42:56.386 --> 01:42:57.546
What'd you say to me?

01:42:57.888 --> 01:43:00.379
I said go answer the door.
What are you, deaf?

01:43:00.724 --> 01:43:02.885
You want me to go answer the door?

01:43:03.227 --> 01:43:05.718
That's right, lunkhead,
go answer the door.

01:43:06.230 --> 01:43:08.755
Or are you too drunk to do that, too?

01:43:08.999 --> 01:43:10.523
There's no need for you to...

01:43:10.734 --> 01:43:12.167
Answer it!

01:43:12.769 --> 01:43:14.532
You be houseboy around here awhile.

01:43:14.738 --> 01:43:16.729
You can start in
being houseboy right now.

01:43:17.074 --> 01:43:18.735
Look, I'm no flunky to you.

01:43:19.076 --> 01:43:21.567
Sure, you are!
You're ambitious, aren't you?

01:43:21.912 --> 01:43:26.076
You didn't come back here with me
out of driven passion, did you?

01:43:26.917 --> 01:43:29.750
You were thinking a little bit
about your career.

01:43:30.621 --> 01:43:35.081
You can just houseboy your way up
the ladder for awhile.

01:43:36.927 --> 01:43:38.258
There's no limit to you, is there?

01:43:38.595 --> 01:43:40.859
No, baby, none. Go answer the door.

01:43:41.164 --> 01:43:42.631
Go on, git!

01:43:44.935 --> 01:43:46.425
Aimless. Wanton.

01:43:46.770 --> 01:43:48.931
Now, you just do as you're told.

01:43:49.273 --> 01:43:51.764
You show ol' Martha
there's something you can do.

01:43:52.109 --> 01:43:54.441
I'm coming, for Christ's sake!

01:43:54.778 --> 01:43:56.439
Wonderful! Marvelous!

01:43:56.780 --> 01:43:59.544
Just a gigolo everywhere I go.

01:43:59.783 --> 01:44:00.477
Stop that!

01:44:01.118 --> 01:44:04.781
Sorry, baby. Now you go
answer the little door, huh?

01:44:13.931 --> 01:44:15.831
How lovely!

01:44:18.302 --> 01:44:21.794
Why, sonny, you came home
for your birthday at last!

01:44:22.272 --> 01:44:23.739
Get away from me!

01:44:24.308 --> 01:44:27.141
That's the houseboy, for God's sake!

01:44:27.477 --> 01:44:31.641
That's not our own little Sonny-Jim,
our own all-American something or other?

01:44:31.982 --> 01:44:35.975
I certainly hope not.
He's been acting awful funny if he is.

01:44:36.320 --> 01:44:38.151
I'll bet. Chippie, chippie, huh?

01:44:40.924 --> 01:44:42.915
I brung these flowers...

01:44:45.262 --> 01:44:46.593
...'cause youse...

01:44:47.397 --> 01:44:49.126
Aw, hell, Martha!

01:44:50.934 --> 01:44:55.598
Pansies, rosemary, violence,
mah wedding bouquet!

01:44:55.939 --> 01:44:57.600
If you don't mind, I'll get my wife...

01:44:59.142 --> 01:45:02.270
You stay right where you are.
Make my hubby a drink.

01:45:02.612 --> 01:45:03.943
I don't think I will.

01:45:04.281 --> 01:45:08.615
No, Martha. That would be too much.
He's your houseboy, not mine.

01:45:08.952 --> 01:45:10.943
I'm nobody's houseboy!

01:45:12.956 --> 01:45:16.915
I'm nobody's houseboy now

01:45:18.562 --> 01:45:19.256
Vicious.

01:45:19.463 --> 01:45:20.953
Children? That right?

01:45:21.298 --> 01:45:25.462
Vicious children with their sad games
hopscotching their way through life?

01:45:25.802 --> 01:45:26.962
Something like that.

01:45:27.304 --> 01:45:28.134
Screw, baby.

01:45:28.472 --> 01:45:31.464
Him can't! Him too full o' booze!

01:45:31.808 --> 01:45:35.141
Really? Here! Dump these in some gin.

01:45:37.848 --> 01:45:40.373
A terrible thing to do
to Martha's snapdragons!

01:45:40.584 --> 01:45:42.142
Is that what they are?

01:45:42.486 --> 01:45:46.650
Yup. And I went by moonlight to Daddy's
greenhouse to pick them for her.

01:45:46.990 --> 01:45:49.823
There is no moon.
I saw it go down from the bedroom.

01:45:50.160 --> 01:45:51.320
From the bedroom?

01:45:53.497 --> 01:45:54.657
There is a moon.

01:45:54.998 --> 01:45:57.489
There is no goddamn moon,
the moon went down.

01:45:57.834 --> 01:45:59.495
That may be, Chastity,
but it came back up.

01:45:59.703 --> 01:46:00.294
Bull!

01:46:00.504 --> 01:46:03.735
Once when I was sailing past Majorca,
the moon went down...

01:46:03.940 --> 01:46:07.000
...thought about it awhile then,
pop, came up again.

01:46:07.344 --> 01:46:10.177
That is not true. That is such a lie!

01:46:10.514 --> 01:46:12.846
You must not call everything a lie.
Must she?

01:46:13.350 --> 01:46:15.341
I don't know when you people are lying.

01:46:16.019 --> 01:46:18.510
- You're damn right!
- You're not supposed to.

01:46:20.123 --> 01:46:24.025
- So, I was sailing past Majorca...
- You never sailed past Majorca.

01:46:24.528 --> 01:46:28.020
You were never in
the Mediterranean at all, ever!

01:46:28.365 --> 01:46:31.357
My mom and dad took me
as a college graduation present.

01:46:32.035 --> 01:46:33.195
After you killed them?

01:46:34.771 --> 01:46:35.897
Maybe.

01:46:37.374 --> 01:46:39.706
Yeah. And maybe not too.

01:46:40.377 --> 01:46:41.309
Jesus!

01:46:41.878 --> 01:46:45.541
Truth and illusion. Who knows
the difference, toots? Houseboy?

01:46:45.882 --> 01:46:46.712
I'm not a houseboy.

01:46:47.050 --> 01:46:50.349
You don't make it in the sack,
you're a houseboy.

01:46:51.221 --> 01:46:52.984
Then you must have made it, yes?

01:46:53.723 --> 01:46:58.057
Somebody's lying, not playing the
game straight. Who's lying? Martha?

01:46:58.895 --> 01:47:00.385
Tell him I'm not a houseboy.

01:47:02.365 --> 01:47:04.230
You're not a houseboy.

01:47:08.405 --> 01:47:09.394
So be it.

01:47:11.408 --> 01:47:14.241
Truth and illusion.
You don't know the difference.

01:47:15.245 --> 01:47:17.736
No, but we must carry on
as though we did.

01:47:18.915 --> 01:47:20.075
Amen.

01:47:21.918 --> 01:47:23.078
Snap went the dragons.

01:47:23.320 --> 01:47:24.150
Thank you.

01:47:25.055 --> 01:47:25.953
Skip it.

01:47:26.256 --> 01:47:27.416
I said snap went the dragons!

01:47:27.691 --> 01:47:29.124
Yeah, we know.

01:47:30.093 --> 01:47:31.082
Don't!

01:47:31.428 --> 01:47:32.588
Don't do that.

01:47:32.929 --> 01:47:33.759
Shut up, stud!

01:47:34.097 --> 01:47:35.086
I'm not a stud.

01:47:35.432 --> 01:47:37.423
Then you're a houseboy. Which is it?

01:47:38.268 --> 01:47:39.929
Does it matter to you?

01:47:40.770 --> 01:47:43.762
No, actually it doesn't.
Either way I've had it.

01:47:44.608 --> 01:47:47.270
Stop throwing these damn things at me!

01:47:47.611 --> 01:47:49.806
- Either way. Snap!
- Shall I do something to him?

01:47:50.113 --> 01:47:51.444
You leave him alone!

01:47:51.781 --> 01:47:54.113
Which are you, baby, houseboy or stud?

01:47:56.620 --> 01:48:00.112
Truth or illusion, George?
Doesn't it matter to you at all?

01:48:03.126 --> 01:48:05.788
Snap! You got your answer, baby.

01:48:11.134 --> 01:48:11.964
Got it.

01:48:16.473 --> 01:48:18.805
You just gird your
blue-veined loins, girl.

01:48:19.309 --> 01:48:22.301
There's one more game to play.
It's called Bringing up Baby.

01:48:23.647 --> 01:48:26.639
I don't want a fuss. Don't want
any scandal around here, do you?

01:48:26.983 --> 01:48:28.814
Want to keep to your timetable?
Then sit!

01:48:29.486 --> 01:48:34.150
And you, pretty miss, you like fun and
games! You're a sport from way back!

01:48:34.491 --> 01:48:35.480
All right.

01:48:35.825 --> 01:48:37.986
Good. But we're not all here.

01:48:40.830 --> 01:48:42.320
Your little wifelet isn't here.

01:48:42.666 --> 01:48:43.997
She had a rough night...

01:48:44.334 --> 01:48:47.667
We can't play without everybody.
We need your little wife.

01:48:50.507 --> 01:48:51.496
Cut that!

01:48:52.509 --> 01:48:55.842
Just get off your butt and bring
that little dip back in here!

01:48:56.179 --> 01:48:59.171
Now be a good puppy, go fetch.
Fetch, good puppy.

01:49:09.459 --> 01:49:10.619
One more game.

01:49:19.135 --> 01:49:20.966
I don't like what's going to happen.

01:49:21.471 --> 01:49:22.802
Do you know what it is?

01:49:23.640 --> 01:49:26.131
No. But I don't like it.

01:49:26.476 --> 01:49:28.137
Maybe you will, Martha.

01:49:29.479 --> 01:49:31.310
It's a real fun game.

01:49:31.648 --> 01:49:32.979
No more games.

01:49:33.316 --> 01:49:37.150
One more, Martha. One more game
and then beddie-bye.

01:49:37.487 --> 01:49:41.821
Everybody packs up his tools
and baggage and stuff and go home.

01:49:42.158 --> 01:49:43.853
And you and me...

01:49:44.394 --> 01:49:46.919
...we're going to climb
them well-worn stairs.

01:49:47.163 --> 01:49:48.824
No, George, no.

01:49:49.165 --> 01:49:50.496
Yes, baby.

01:49:51.835 --> 01:49:53.996
It'll all be done before you know it.

01:49:54.838 --> 01:49:56.829
No climb stairs with Georgie?

01:49:57.173 --> 01:50:01.507
No more games. It's games I don't want.
No more games, please.

01:50:01.845 --> 01:50:05.679
Sure you do. Original game girl!
Of course you do.

01:50:08.852 --> 01:50:10.683
Don't you touch me!

01:50:11.454 --> 01:50:13.149
Keep your paws clean
for the undergraduates.

01:50:15.258 --> 01:50:16.247
Listen to me!

01:50:16.493 --> 01:50:17.824
You've had an evening.

01:50:18.028 --> 01:50:22.556
You can't stop when there's enough
blood in your mouth. We're going on.

01:50:22.832 --> 01:50:26.529
I'm having at you, and your performance
will look like an Easter pageant.

01:50:26.870 --> 01:50:28.098
Get yourself alert.

01:50:28.405 --> 01:50:29.895
- Get some life in you.
- Stop!

01:50:30.106 --> 01:50:31.368
Pull yourself together!

01:50:31.708 --> 01:50:34.871
I'm going to knock you around
and I want you up for it!

01:50:35.845 --> 01:50:37.005
What do you want?

01:50:37.213 --> 01:50:39.044
- An equal battle.
- You'll get it.

01:50:39.249 --> 01:50:41.717
- I want you mad.
- I'm mad. Don't worry about it!

01:50:42.452 --> 01:50:44.545
Good girl!
We'll play to the death.

01:50:44.754 --> 01:50:46.551
- Yours?
- You'll be surprised.

01:50:46.890 --> 01:50:48.221
Here come the tots. Be ready.

01:50:48.558 --> 01:50:49.547
I'm ready for you.

01:50:50.026 --> 01:50:52.358
Hip, hop. Hip, hip, hop.

01:50:52.562 --> 01:50:54.723
Are you a bunny, honey!

01:50:55.065 --> 01:50:57.295
- How's the bunny?
- Bunny funny!

01:50:57.734 --> 01:50:59.224
Bunny funny. Good for bunny.

01:50:59.736 --> 01:51:00.896
Honey funny bunny.

01:51:03.073 --> 01:51:04.438
All right, here we go.

01:51:04.708 --> 01:51:06.403
Last game. All sit.

01:51:07.577 --> 01:51:11.377
- Sit down. This is a civilized game.
- Just get on with it.

01:51:11.915 --> 01:51:15.908
I think we've been having a real good
evening, all things considered.

01:51:16.252 --> 01:51:19.085
We've got to know each other.
And we've had fun and games.

01:51:19.923 --> 01:51:21.254
Like Curl Up On The Floor.

01:51:21.458 --> 01:51:22.152
The Tiles.

01:51:22.425 --> 01:51:23.858
The Tiles, Snap The Dragon.

01:51:24.260 --> 01:51:25.090
Peel the Label!

01:51:26.262 --> 01:51:28.253
Label. Peel the Label.

01:51:28.598 --> 01:51:30.088
I peel labels.

01:51:30.300 --> 01:51:32.268
We all peel labels, sweetie.

01:51:32.602 --> 01:51:35.594
When you get through the skin,
and through the muscle...

01:51:35.939 --> 01:51:40.103
...and slosh aside the organs, down to
the bone, you know what you do?

01:51:41.277 --> 01:51:42.938
When you get down to the bone...

01:51:43.279 --> 01:51:45.770
...you aren't all the way.
Something's inside the bone.

01:51:46.116 --> 01:51:48.277
The marrow.
That's what you got to get at.

01:51:48.785 --> 01:51:51.948
But bones are pretty resilient,
especially in the young.

01:51:52.288 --> 01:51:53.448
Now take our son...

01:51:56.126 --> 01:51:58.117
Our son. Martha's and my little joy.

01:52:00.230 --> 01:52:01.595
Just what are you doing?

01:52:01.798 --> 01:52:04.198
- I'm talking about our son.
- Well, don't.

01:52:04.634 --> 01:52:06.795
I want to.
It's important we talk about him.

01:52:07.137 --> 01:52:10.129
You want to hear about our
bouncy boy, don't you?

01:52:11.641 --> 01:52:13.632
Martha's and my son.

01:52:16.146 --> 01:52:17.477
You have a child?

01:52:17.814 --> 01:52:19.975
Yes indeed, do we ever!

01:52:20.316 --> 01:52:21.806
Will you talk about him or shall I?

01:52:22.018 --> 01:52:24.680
- Don't.
- All rightie, now let's see.

01:52:24.888 --> 01:52:26.651
He's nice, despite home his life.

01:52:26.990 --> 01:52:30.824
Most kids would be neurotic,
Martha carrying on the way she does.

01:52:31.161 --> 01:52:34.324
Sleeping till 4 p.m.
Climbing over the poor bastard...

01:52:34.664 --> 01:52:39.158
...trying to break the bathroom door
to wash him in the tub when he's 16.

01:52:39.669 --> 01:52:41.830
Dragging strangers
to the house all hours.

01:52:43.673 --> 01:52:44.833
That's enough.

01:52:45.175 --> 01:52:46.403
Do you want to take over?

01:52:46.743 --> 01:52:49.337
Why would anyone want to
wash a 16 year-old?

01:52:49.679 --> 01:52:51.010
For Christ's sake!

01:52:51.347 --> 01:52:52.439
Well, why?

01:52:52.649 --> 01:52:54.173
Because it's her baby-poo.

01:52:54.517 --> 01:52:55.677
All right.

01:52:56.019 --> 01:52:59.011
Our son, you want our son?
You'll have it.

01:53:01.858 --> 01:53:03.018
Do you want a drink?

01:53:07.030 --> 01:53:09.521
We don't have to hear it
if you don't want to.

01:53:09.866 --> 01:53:12.357
Who says? You in a position
to set the rules?

01:53:14.704 --> 01:53:16.194
Good boy. You'll go far.

01:53:17.040 --> 01:53:19.031
All right, your recitation please.

01:53:25.014 --> 01:53:26.106
Our son...

01:53:26.382 --> 01:53:27.314
All right!

01:53:28.384 --> 01:53:29.544
Our son.

01:53:32.055 --> 01:53:36.048
Our son was born in a September night,
a night not unlike tonight...

01:53:38.061 --> 01:53:39.323
...though tomorrow...

01:53:40.163 --> 01:53:41.926
...and sixteen years ago.

01:53:42.131 --> 01:53:43.496
See, I told you.

01:53:44.901 --> 01:53:48.337
- It was an easy birth.
- No, you labored, how you labored!

01:53:48.738 --> 01:53:50.228
It was an easy birth!

01:53:51.074 --> 01:53:52.837
Once it had been...

01:53:53.042 --> 01:53:54.407
...accepted.

01:53:55.245 --> 01:53:58.043
- Relaxed into.
- That's better.

01:53:59.082 --> 01:54:02.415
It was an easy birth,
once it had been accepted.

01:54:03.920 --> 01:54:05.581
And I was young.

01:54:05.922 --> 01:54:07.685
And he was healthy...

01:54:08.758 --> 01:54:11.090
...a red, bawling child.

01:54:11.594 --> 01:54:13.960
Martha thinks she saw him at delivery.

01:54:14.430 --> 01:54:16.591
With slippery, firm limbs.

01:54:17.767 --> 01:54:21.601
And a full head of black, fine hair.

01:54:22.772 --> 01:54:24.103
Which, later...

01:54:24.774 --> 01:54:25.934
...later became...

01:54:28.011 --> 01:54:29.444
...blond as the sun.

01:54:31.114 --> 01:54:32.445
Our son.

01:54:32.782 --> 01:54:34.113
He was a healthy child.

01:54:35.618 --> 01:54:39.452
And I had wanted a child.
Oh, I had wanted a child!

01:54:39.789 --> 01:54:41.450
A son? Daughter?

01:54:41.791 --> 01:54:42.780
A child!

01:54:47.797 --> 01:54:49.458
I had my child.

01:54:49.799 --> 01:54:50.959
Our child.

01:54:53.970 --> 01:54:55.403
And we raised him.

01:54:58.308 --> 01:55:00.299
Yes, we did. We raised him.

01:55:03.646 --> 01:55:06.809
And he had green eyes.

01:55:08.818 --> 01:55:12.481
Such green, green eyes.

01:55:13.656 --> 01:55:15.487
Blue, green, brown.

01:55:16.492 --> 01:55:18.187
And he loved the sun.

01:55:18.494 --> 01:55:21.930
And he was tan
before and after everyone.

01:55:24.000 --> 01:55:25.592
And in the sun...

01:55:26.502 --> 01:55:27.992
...his hair became...

01:55:29.038 --> 01:55:30.130
...fleece.

01:55:34.177 --> 01:55:37.169
Beautiful, beautiful boy.

01:55:42.518 --> 01:55:45.351
So beautiful, so wise.

01:55:45.855 --> 01:55:47.345
All truth being relative.

01:55:48.358 --> 01:55:49.689
It was true.

01:55:51.361 --> 01:55:53.693
Beautiful, wise, perfect!

01:55:53.896 --> 01:55:55.523
There's a real mother talking.

01:55:55.832 --> 01:55:57.697
I want a child!

01:55:59.369 --> 01:56:00.358
On principle?

01:56:00.703 --> 01:56:03.194
I want a child. I want a baby.

01:56:03.706 --> 01:56:05.867
This perfection could not last.

01:56:06.876 --> 01:56:08.434
Not with George.

01:56:09.646 --> 01:56:10.977
Not with George around.

01:56:11.180 --> 01:56:12.647
There, you see, I knew she'd shift.

01:56:12.849 --> 01:56:14.510
- Be still!
- Sorry, Mother.

01:56:14.717 --> 01:56:16.048
Can't you be still?

01:56:16.886 --> 01:56:21.380
Not with George. A drowning man takes
down those nearest, and he tried.

01:56:22.058 --> 01:56:25.050
And, God, how I fought him!
How I fought him!

01:56:25.395 --> 01:56:26.726
The one thing...

01:56:27.063 --> 01:56:29.554
...I tried to carry unscathed
through the...

01:56:30.566 --> 01:56:31.897
...sewer of our marriage...

01:56:32.402 --> 01:56:36.065
...through the sick nights and the
pathetic, stupid days...

01:56:36.406 --> 01:56:39.739
...through the derision and the
laughter. God, the laughter!

01:56:41.077 --> 01:56:43.671
Through one failure after another.

01:56:44.080 --> 01:56:47.914
Each attempt more numbing,
more sickening than the one before.

01:56:48.751 --> 01:56:52.084
The one thing, the one person
I tried to protect...

01:56:52.755 --> 01:56:57.249
...to raise above the mire of this vile,
crushing marriage...

01:56:58.094 --> 01:57:02.087
...the one light in all this
hopeless darkness! Our son!

01:57:02.298 --> 01:57:02.821
Stop it!

01:57:07.737 --> 01:57:09.204
Why, don't you like it?

01:57:09.605 --> 01:57:10.970
You can't do this.

01:57:11.174 --> 01:57:11.765
Who says?

01:57:11.974 --> 01:57:14.272
- I say!
- Tell us why, baby.

01:57:15.278 --> 01:57:16.768
Is this game over?

01:57:19.282 --> 01:57:21.273
Oh, no! Not by a long shot.

01:57:22.285 --> 01:57:25.118
I've got a surprise for you.
It's about sonny-Jim.

01:57:27.123 --> 01:57:28.613
I'm running this show!

01:57:29.625 --> 01:57:30.614
Sweetheart...

01:57:31.360 --> 01:57:34.090
...I’m afraid I've got
some bad news for you.

01:57:34.297 --> 01:57:36.629
For both of us, I mean.
Some rather sad news.

01:57:37.567 --> 01:57:39.091
What is this?

01:57:39.302 --> 01:57:43.295
Martha, while you were busy,
while the two of you were busy...

01:57:43.639 --> 01:57:45.630
...I don't know where,
but you were somewhere...

01:57:46.142 --> 01:57:47.973
...while you were busy for awhile...

01:57:48.811 --> 01:57:51.507
...Missy and I
were having a little talk.

01:57:51.714 --> 01:57:53.773
You know, a chaw and a talk.

01:57:53.983 --> 01:57:55.746
And the doorbell rang.

01:57:55.952 --> 01:57:56.976
Chimed.

01:58:03.493 --> 01:58:04.824
It's hard for me to tell you.

01:58:06.462 --> 01:58:07.759
Please don't!

01:58:07.997 --> 01:58:08.986
Tell me!

01:58:09.999 --> 01:58:13.992
It was good old Western Union,
some little boy about seventy.

01:58:15.004 --> 01:58:15.936
Crazy Billy?

01:58:16.339 --> 01:58:17.829
That's right. Crazy Billy.

01:58:18.508 --> 01:58:20.999
And he had a telegram and it was for us.

01:58:23.012 --> 01:58:24.172
I have to tell you about it.

01:58:25.681 --> 01:58:30.015
Why did they bring it?
Why didn't they telephone it?

01:58:30.520 --> 01:58:35.184
There are some telegrams you have to
deliver, Martha. Some you cannot phone.

01:58:36.492 --> 01:58:37.823
What do you mean?

01:58:40.530 --> 01:58:42.191
I can hardly bring myself to say it.

01:58:43.166 --> 01:58:44.292
You want to do it?

01:58:50.039 --> 01:58:54.533
Well, Martha, I'm afraid our boy
isn't coming home for his birthday.

01:58:55.378 --> 01:58:56.868
Of course he is!

01:58:57.713 --> 01:58:59.374
Of course he is! I say he is!

01:58:59.715 --> 01:59:00.545
He can't.

01:59:04.921 --> 01:59:06.149
Our son...

01:59:07.223 --> 01:59:08.212
...is...

01:59:09.792 --> 01:59:10.486
...dead.

01:59:12.228 --> 01:59:14.890
He was killed late in the afternoon...

01:59:15.565 --> 01:59:17.829
...on a country road with his
learner's permit.

01:59:18.034 --> 01:59:20.559
He swerved to avoid a porcupine
and drove...

01:59:20.903 --> 01:59:22.063
You can't do that!

01:59:23.072 --> 01:59:24.403
...into a large tree.

01:59:25.541 --> 01:59:27.031
You cannot do that!

01:59:28.711 --> 01:59:30.235
I thought you should know.

01:59:31.981 --> 01:59:33.710
You cannot do that!

01:59:34.050 --> 01:59:36.883
You can't decide these things
for yourself!

01:59:37.553 --> 01:59:39.384
I will not let you do that!

01:59:39.722 --> 01:59:41.383
Have to leave around noon, I suppose.

01:59:41.724 --> 01:59:43.749
I won't let you decide these things.

01:59:43.960 --> 01:59:47.225
There are matters of identification,
arrangements to be made.

01:59:47.563 --> 01:59:49.724
You can't do this! I won't let you!

01:59:50.399 --> 01:59:53.232
- Get your hands off me!
- I haven't done anything!

01:59:53.569 --> 01:59:55.867
Now you listen to me. Our son is dead!

01:59:56.072 --> 01:59:57.733
Can you get that through your head?

01:59:58.741 --> 02:00:03.075
Listen carefully. We got a telegram.
There was a car accident and he's dead!

02:00:03.412 --> 02:00:06.074
Poof! Just like that!
Now how do you like it?

02:00:10.253 --> 02:00:12.244
Let her go.
She'll be all right.

02:00:23.432 --> 02:00:25.798
He is not dead.

02:00:28.271 --> 02:00:29.260
He is dead.

02:00:34.610 --> 02:00:36.942
You cannot decide.

02:00:37.947 --> 02:00:39.437
He hasn't decided anything.

02:00:39.782 --> 02:00:42.945
It's not his doing.
He doesn't have the power.

02:00:43.286 --> 02:00:47.620
That's right. I'm no god. I have
no power over life and death, do I?

02:00:49.492 --> 02:00:51.619
You can't kill him.

02:00:52.028 --> 02:00:54.519
You can't let him die!

02:00:59.435 --> 02:01:00.800
There was a telegram.

02:01:04.507 --> 02:01:07.806
Show it to me! Show me that telegram!

02:01:12.815 --> 02:01:13.804
I ate it.

02:01:15.151 --> 02:01:17.312
What did you just say to me?

02:01:18.354 --> 02:01:20.982
I ate it.

02:01:24.327 --> 02:01:25.658
Good for you, Martha.

02:01:26.329 --> 02:01:29.264
You make a joke at a time like this?

02:01:29.465 --> 02:01:30.796
Did I not eat the telegram?

02:01:31.000 --> 02:01:33.833
You ate it. I watched you
and you ate it all down.

02:01:34.170 --> 02:01:35.159
Like a good boy.

02:01:36.772 --> 02:01:38.603
You won't get away with this.

02:01:40.843 --> 02:01:43.175
You know the rules, for God's sake!

02:01:44.513 --> 02:01:46.003
What are you talking about?

02:01:46.349 --> 02:01:47.680
I can kill him if I want to.

02:01:48.017 --> 02:01:49.075
He is our child.

02:01:49.285 --> 02:01:52.584
- You bore him. A good delivery.
- He is our child.

02:01:52.788 --> 02:01:54.016
And I've killed him.

02:01:56.392 --> 02:01:58.917
Oh my God, I think I understand this.

02:01:59.362 --> 02:02:00.294
Do you?

02:02:01.063 --> 02:02:04.362
- Oh my God, I think I understand this.
- Good for you.

02:02:09.138 --> 02:02:12.335
You've no right.
You've no right at all.

02:02:12.541 --> 02:02:17.001
I have the right, we never spoke of it.
I could kill him any time I wanted.

02:02:17.246 --> 02:02:18.907
Why?

02:02:19.215 --> 02:02:20.443
You broke our rule, Martha.

02:02:20.683 --> 02:02:24.244
You mentioned him to somebody else.

02:02:24.553 --> 02:02:26.384
- I did not.
- Yes, you did.

02:02:29.925 --> 02:02:31.893
To me, you mentioned him to me.

02:02:35.064 --> 02:02:36.224
I forget.

02:02:37.566 --> 02:02:41.525
Sometimes when it's late night
and everybody's talking...

02:02:41.904 --> 02:02:43.895
...I forget and I want to mention him.

02:02:44.240 --> 02:02:46.902
But I hold on. I hold on.

02:02:48.277 --> 02:02:50.905
I've wanted to so often.

02:02:51.914 --> 02:02:53.905
But, George, you've pushed it.

02:02:54.250 --> 02:02:57.413
There was no need,
there was no need for this!

02:02:59.088 --> 02:03:00.919
I mentioned him, all right?

02:03:02.258 --> 02:03:04.749
But you didn't have
to push it over the edge.

02:03:05.594 --> 02:03:07.585
You didn't have to kill him.

02:03:15.604 --> 02:03:19.096
You didn't have to have him die.

02:03:24.814 --> 02:03:27.442
That wasn't needed.

02:03:57.146 --> 02:03:58.670
It's dawn.

02:04:00.249 --> 02:04:02.080
I think the party's over.

02:04:07.990 --> 02:04:09.651
You couldn't have any?

02:04:12.361 --> 02:04:13.589
We couldn't.

02:04:18.501 --> 02:04:21.299
Home to bed, children.
It's way past your bedtime.

02:04:32.281 --> 02:04:33.748
You two go now.

02:04:48.030 --> 02:04:49.861
- I'd like to...
- Goodnight.

02:05:17.026 --> 02:05:18.391
You want anything?

02:05:19.728 --> 02:05:21.218
No. Nothing.

02:05:27.036 --> 02:05:28.367
Time for bed.

02:05:35.077 --> 02:05:36.135
Tired?

02:05:36.512 --> 02:05:37.536
Yes.

02:05:38.847 --> 02:05:39.836
I am.

02:05:49.225 --> 02:05:50.749
Sunday tomorrow.

02:05:53.195 --> 02:05:54.389
All day.

02:06:32.034 --> 02:06:34.059
Did you have to?

02:06:36.105 --> 02:06:37.129
Yes.

02:06:41.977 --> 02:06:43.342
You had to?

02:06:49.985 --> 02:06:51.077
I don't know.

02:06:54.657 --> 02:06:56.852
- It was time.
- Was it?

02:07:08.170 --> 02:07:09.603
I'm cold.

02:07:12.174 --> 02:07:13.232
It's late.

02:07:25.788 --> 02:07:27.255
It will be better.

02:07:30.626 --> 02:07:32.059
I don't know.

02:07:33.195 --> 02:07:34.924
It will be. Maybe.

02:07:37.366 --> 02:07:39.197
I'm not sure.

02:07:48.043 --> 02:07:49.237
Just us?

02:07:53.716 --> 02:07:55.411
- You don't suppose maybe...
- No.

02:08:09.465 --> 02:08:11.126
- You all right?
- Yes.

02:08:16.972 --> 02:08:17.939
No.

02:08:23.078 --> 02:08:26.536
Who's afraid of Virginia Woolf?

02:08:28.884 --> 02:08:30.215
I am, George.

02:08:33.922 --> 02:08:35.219
I am, George.

02:08:37.226 --> 02:08:38.318
I am.

